CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper January 5, 1963, pg. 7, reads: "Landmark Goes - A crane bites into a section of the roof of the Pennsylvania Railroad's East Liberty station, which will be disappearing after more than 50 years of service to commuters. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Pennsylvania Railroad East Liberty train station being razed, with crane on left in background
